==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shedder
<hw>Shed"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, sheds; <as>as, a <ex>shedder</ex> of blood; a
<ex>shedder</ex> of tears</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A crab in the act of casting its
shell, or immediately afterwards while still soft; -- applied especially
to the edible crabs, which are most prized while in this
state.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shedding</ent>⟦br⟧
